diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: The patient presented with worsening periumbilical pain that later localized to the right lower quadrant (RLQ), accompanied by nausea and vomiting. Physical examination revealed tenderness in the RLQ > periumbilical without rebound or guarding. CT findings included non-hemorrhagic free fluid and hyperdense fluid compatible with hemoperitoneum, and the appendix was surgically absent post-laparoscopic appendectomy.
